place.name: SNETTERTON
place.gazetteerText: SNETTERTON, a parish in Wayland district, Norfolk; 2 miles NNE of Harling-Road r. station, and 4½ SW of Attleborough. Post town, Thetford. Acres, 2,189. Real property, £2,155. Pop., 237. Houses, 59. The manor belongs to the Earl of Albemarle. The living is a rectory, annexed to Quiddenham. The church is good. Charities, £7. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
